  <compounddef id="MEMALLOC" kind="page">
    <compoundname>MEMALLOC</compoundname>
    <title>MEMALLOC Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">MEMALLOC(integer-expression)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Allocates a block of <bold>heap memory</bold> of the given size (in bytes) and returns a <bold>pointer/integer handle</bold> to it.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="MEMALLOC_1autotoc_md285">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">size<sp/>=<sp/>FILESIZE(&quot;/system/webserver/logo.png&quot;)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">buf<sp/><sp/>=<sp/>MEMALLOC(size)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>...<sp/>use<sp/>buf<sp/>with<sp/>BINREAD<sp/>/<sp/>SOCKBINWRITE<sp/>...</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">MEMRELEASE<sp/>buf</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="MEMALLOC_1autotoc_md287">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Contents are unspecified on allocation.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Always pair with <ref refid="MEMRELEASE" kindref="compound">MEMRELEASE</ref> to avoid leaks.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The allocated memory is only valid while the program that requested it is running. The returned value ma be passed to other programs, however be aware of this restriction.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Returned handle is suitable for binary I/O (<ref refid="BINREAD" kindref="compound">BINREAD</ref>, <ref refid="BINWRITE" kindref="compound">BINWRITE</ref>, <ref refid="SOCKBINWRITE" kindref="compound">SOCKBINWRITE</ref>, <ref refid="SOCKBINREAD" kindref="compound">SOCKBINREAD</ref>).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Once the program ends, all memory requested by MEMALLOC is automatically freed.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><bold>See also:</bold> <ref refid="MEMRELEASE" kindref="compound">MEMRELEASE</ref> · <ref refid="BINREAD" kindref="compound">BINREAD</ref> · <ref refid="BINWRITE" kindref="compound">BINWRITE</ref> </para>
</sect3>
